        <head xml:id="pl-l4d2c3-Hd1e109">CAP. III</head>
        <p xml:id="pl-l4d2c3-d1e112">
          The baptism of John was into penitence, 
          not into remission; 
          but the baptism of Christ was into remission; 
          because while baptizing John called men to penitence, 
          and those who he was baptizing, he taught penitence, 
          according to which it says:  
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pl-l4d2c3-Qd1e116" ana="#mt3_6">
              They came to John in the Jordan, 
              confessing their sins
            </quote>
            <bibl>Matthew 3:6</bibl>
          </cit>. 
          But in the baptism of John 
          there is not remission of sin, 
          which there is in the baptism of Christ.
        </p>
      </div>
